message:
@llimllib How are you getting the data out of HTML? Your HTML parser can unescape for you—lxml.html does this by default and BeautifulSoup does this if asked to.

Usually when I hear someone asking this, it's because they're trying to extract data from HTML using regular expressions. However, parsing HTML with regex is not just bad form, it's *provably impossible*.

Using lxml.html as an HTML parser is preferable to BeautifulSoup. BeautifulSoup is on ultra-low-maintainable mode and the creator wishes he could abandon it. There are no plans for it to ever work well with 3.x, but lxml.html works great on 3.x.
